name: Méthanosaure
trivia: Dragons who love giving humans a good fright by inflating themselves and then making themselves burst. In order to get the biggest bang they can, they inhale huge volumes of air but occasionally wimp out before they pop.

name: Gloutofourmilier
trivia: These long-snouted  monsters resemble spiny anteaters. Their lengthy tongues are well-adapted to slurping army ants up from their nests.

name: Poids-coq
trivia: These thumping great chickens have learned how to fly. Thanks to their highly-developed flight muscles, they can strike with the power of trained puglist.

name: Dingo bongo
trivia: Sturdy spirits in the thrall of their large-faced bongos. All manner of monsters are drawn in by their deft drumming, entranced by the intricate rhapsody of rhythm.

name: Gluanbulle
trivia: These unfortunate creatures were once normal slimes until permeated by swamp poison, causing their bodies to collapse like underbaked meringue.

name: Lapicorne
trivia: These creatures might resemble rabbits, but meet one of their horns head-on and you'll understand the difference rather sharpish. They pass the long nights huddled together in their warrens.

name: Piperaduo
trivia: These terrible twins are in fact born already skewered. Always butting heads, they are often witnessed mid-argument.

name: Cyclown
trivia: These wicked wing spirits sport their whirlwinds like work attire. Their greatest desire is to welcome wanders into their whirling worlds.

name: Damoisel
trivia: These dragons  like to ensorcell travellers with their beautiful fairy wings. Not only bewitching to behold, their wings release a fine powder which puts their prey in a trance.

name: Vampivol
trivia: These flapping pains in the neck only come out at night. They love nothing more than slurping up human blood, the fresher the better.

name: Dragronce
trivia: Cursed thickets of thorn tangled into draconic shape. Those entwine in their terrifying clutches have no hope of escape.

name: Kotonfatal
trivia: This fluffball is covered in green fur from top to toe. Though easily spooked, those with sharp eyes might spot something funny where this beastie's nose should be before it scrapers.

name: Feu follet
trivia: No-one knows for certain how these monsters came to be. Some believe they were born of the fiery 'Frizz' spell, while others thing they are the soulds of those who died with a burning desire for revenge.

name: Chienfernal
trivia: Hellish hounds employed in the underworld as ghastly guard dogs. Bloodthirsty to the bone, even fellow monsters give these mutts a wide berth.

name: Champigoule
trivia: These great big gurning mushrooms spring up in their dozens in damp locales. They propagate by putting travellers to sleep and seeding them with their spores.

name: Fantôme
trivia: Unfinished business in their previous lives prevents these poltergeists from ever being at peace. They're always trying to inflict to a fright one way or another, just for the attention.

name: Médigluant
trivia: These soft-centred slimes simply cannot stand by when they spy someone in need. Word has it there's one in particular who travels far and wide in pursuit of his dreams of becoming human.

name: Khalamarmot
trivia: These squid-like squirts are baby khalamari. Though small in stature, they're as tough as any full-grown sea-dweller.

name: Furibombyx
trivia: Though these creepy-crawlies might look like larvae, they are in fact fully grown. They keep themselves warm in cold weather by rolling up into snug little balls.

name: Komodor
trivia: Nippy little dragons who have learned to stand on their highly-developed hind legs. At full pelt, they can outpace a racehorse, but haven't yet mastered the subtle art of slowing down.

name: Lampiste
trivia: These sparky spirits inhabit lanterns that have been discarded by their owners. They like to terrify unfortunate adventurers who tramp their terrain at night.

name: Bouclieux
trivia: These shy scoundrels dish out damage from behind their smirking shields, which are precious family heirlooms, passed down from father to son.

name: Bisebave
trivia: Who could resist that king-sized kisser? Protective of their prime assets, you won't catch one of these full-lipped fiends without their trusty lip balm.

name: Luna-tique
trivia: These curious monsters' enormous eyeballs afford them excellent vision, even in absolute darkness. Once they set their sights on their prey, they will not give up until they wrap their tentacles around it.

name: Dingopode
trivia: These monsters have two mouths, one at each end. The one at the front is a strict vegetarian, while the one on the tail is meat mad.

name: Pataupe
trivia: These tunnelling tykes traditionally loved to play pranks, but these days tend to keep their heads down and focus on digging.

name: Zombeagle
trivia: These cadaverous canines originally died of exhaustion before being brought back to life by the powers of darkness, though any smarts they had are long gone.

name: Ombre
trivia: These monsters are said to have been born in the depths of an unfathomably deep darkness. Adept at imitation, they can even forget their natural appearance if they spend long enough shadowing someone else.

name: Gluante
trivia: These slimes are proud of their quirky colouration, which is likely the product of a genetic fluke. They feel faintly warm to the touch.

name: Squelette
trivia: Recycled from the bodies of fallen warriors, these unfortunate cadavers truly get worked to the bone.

name: Gluant
trivia: Adored by all for its flexy physique and funny face, this little monster is something of an icon. Who wouldn't want one for a pal?

name: Corbarbac
trivia: These creepy corvids can't resist scooping up skulls from ancient battlefields. Fledgling ravens like to clamber through the eye-holes to hide from predators.

name: Souche louche
trivia: The tragic remains of chopped-down trees whose deep-seated malice has made them morph into monsters. They attack travellers who try to sit on them, sucking out all their nutrients before discarding the husk.

name: Sanguini vache
trivia: Baby monsters known for their distinctive bovine markings. Considered to be fully-grown once the black fur grows out, replaced entirely with a ravishing shade of rose pink.

name: Combatracien
trivia: These ample amphibians might have mutated into mega-sized monsters, but they retain their original love for croaking out a tune. They like to put on evening concerts just after the rain lets up.

name: Triple burger
trivia: The ripe tomato slime, juicy burger slime and lightly toasted bun slime are a match made in slime heaven. They might look like a tempting meal in waiting, but they don't appreciate being bitten.

name: Dracorolle
trivia: Dragons which live in harmony with herbs and flowers. Theey love nothing more than basking in the sun and will get together to lap up the sun's rays on summer days.

name: Slurpillon
trivia: Slimes which sprouted wings aftrer dreaming of soaring through the sky. Their wings double up as a snug sleeping bag at night.

name: Colèrgine
trivia: These adorable vegetable-based monsters are proud of their ability to cut some rug. Any travaeller straying into their terrain should be prepared to see them strut their stuff.
